{
  "texts": [
    "By contrast, a traditional poll can easily be audited by having access to the underlying data, and simply adding up the numbers.",
    "There is therefore a trade-off: the increased frequency and granularity have to be weighed against a decrease in transparency.",
    "Given the potential consequences, such as the distortion of electoral preferences and outcomes via the injection of unreliable cues, AI polling represents a systematic risk to the electoral process.",
    "It is crucial to hold AI pollsters accountable in the same way as we do with traditional pollsters.",
    "This is due to the potential that they have to influence the outcomes of elections."
  ]
}